content.name: powerSupply
content.description: (Applies to physical deployments only.) Information about power supplies in the storage system.

attributes.name: id
attributes.description: Unique identifier of the powerSupply instance.

attributes.name: health
attributes.description: Health information for the power supply, as defined by the health resource  type.

attributes.name: needsReplacement
attributes.description:
Indicates whether the power supply needs replacement. Values are:
  • true - Power supply needs replacement.
  • false - Power supply does not need replacement.

attributes.name: parent
attributes.description: Resource type and unique identifier for the power supply's parent enclosure.

attributes.name: parentDpe
attributes.description: Parent Disk Processor Enclosure (DPE) of the power supply.

attributes.name: vendorSerialNumber
attributes.description: Vendor serial number for the power supply.

attributes.name: vendorPartNumber
attributes.description: Vendor part number for the power supply.

attributes.name: firmwareVersion
attributes.description: Firmware version number for the power supply.

attributes.name: emcSerialNumber
attributes.description: EMC serial number for the power supply.

attributes.name: parentDae
attributes.description: Parent Disk Array Enclosures (DAE) of the power supply.

attributes.name: slotNumber
attributes.description: Slot number where the power supply is located in the parent enclosure.

attributes.name: model
attributes.description: Manufacturer's model number for the power supply.

attributes.name: emcPartNumber
attributes.description: EMC part number for the power supply.

attributes.name: storageProcessor
attributes.description: Storage Processor that the power supply is associated to.
